Paper: hep-th/9609103

Date: 1996-09-12

Title: Feynman diagrams with the effective action

Authors: M.J. de la Plata and L.L. Salcedo

Comments: Extended revised version. RevTex, 19 pages, 10 figures

Journal-ref: J.Phys. A31 (1998) 4021-4035

A derivation is given of the Feynman rules to be used in the perturbativecomputation of the Green's functions of a generic quantum many-body theory whenthe action which is being perturbed is not necessarily quadratic. Someapplications are discussed.